36#define CH7xxx_REG_VID 0x4a
37#define CH7xxx_REG_DID 0x4b
38
39#define CH7011_VID 0x83 /* 7010 as well */
40#define CH7010B_VID 0x05
41#define CH7009A_VID 0x84
42#define CH7009B_VID 0x85
43#define CH7301_VID 0x95
44
45#define CH7xxx_VID 0x84
46#define CH7xxx_DID 0x17
47#define CH7010_DID 0x16
48
49#define CH7xxx_NUM_REGS 0x4c
50
51#define CH7xxx_CM 0x1c
52#define CH7xxx_CM_XCM (1<<0)
53#define CH7xxx_CM_MCP (1<<2)
54#define CH7xxx_INPUT_CLOCK 0x1d
55#define CH7xxx_GPIO 0x1e
56#define CH7xxx_GPIO_HPIR (1<<3)
57#define CH7xxx_IDF 0x1f
58
59#define CH7xxx_IDF_HSP (1<<3)
60#define CH7xxx_IDF_VSP (1<<4)
61
62#define CH7xxx_CONNECTION_DETECT 0x20
63#define CH7xxx_CDET_DVI (1<<5)
64
65#define CH7301_DAC_CNTL 0x21
66#define CH7301_HOTPLUG 0x23
67#define CH7xxx_TCTL 0x31
68#define CH7xxx_TVCO 0x32
69#define CH7xxx_TPCP 0x33
70#define CH7xxx_TPD 0x34
71#define CH7xxx_TPVT 0x35
72#define CH7xxx_TLPF 0x36
73#define CH7xxx_TCT 0x37
74#define CH7301_TEST_PATTERN 0x48
75
76#define CH7xxx_PM 0x49
77#define CH7xxx_PM_FPD (1<<0)
78#define CH7301_PM_DACPD0 (1<<1)
79#define CH7301_PM_DACPD1 (1<<2)
80#define CH7301_PM_DACPD2 (1<<3)
81#define CH7xxx_PM_DVIL (1<<6)
82#define CH7xxx_PM_DVIP (1<<7)
83
84#define CH7301_SYNC_POLARITY 0x56
85#define CH7301_SYNC_RGB_YUV (1<<0)
86#define CH7301_SYNC_POL_DVI (1<<5)
87
88/** @file
89 * driver for the Chrontel 7xxx DVI chip over DVO.
90 */
91
92static struct ch7xxx_id_struct {
93 uint8_t vid;
94 const char *name;
95} ch7xxx_ids[] = {
96 { CH7011_VID, "CH7011" },
97 { CH7010B_VID, "CH7010B" },
98 { CH7009A_VID, "CH7009A" },
99 { CH7009B_VID, "CH7009B" },
100 { CH7301_VID, "CH7301" },
101};
102
103static struct ch7xxx_did_struct {
104 uint8_t did;
105 const char *name;
106} ch7xxx_dids[] = {
107 { CH7xxx_DID, "CH7XXX" },
108 { CH7010_DID, "CH7010B" },
109};
110
111struct ch7xxx_priv {
112 bool quiet;
113};
114
115static const char *ch7xxx_get_id(uint8_t vid)
116{
117 int i;
118
119 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(ch7xxx_ids); i++) {
120 if (ch7xxx_ids[i].vid == vid)
121 return ch7xxx_ids[i].name;
122 }
123
124 return NULL;
125}
126
127static const char *ch7xxx_get_did(uint8_t did)
128{
129 int i;
130
131 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(ch7xxx_dids); i++) {
132 if (ch7xxx_dids[i].did == did)
133 return ch7xxx_dids[i].name;
134 }
135
136 return NULL;
137}
138
139/** Reads an 8 bit register */
140static bool ch7xxx_readb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t *ch)
141{
142 struct ch7xxx_priv *ch7xxx = dvo->dev_priv;
143 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
144 u8 out_buf[2];
145 u8 in_buf[2];
146
147 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
148 {
149 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
150 .flags = 0,
151 .len = 1,
152 .buf = out_buf,
153 },
154 {
155 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
156 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
157 .len = 1,
158 .buf = in_buf,
159 }
160 };
161
162 out_buf[0] = addr;
163 out_buf[1] = 0;
164
165 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, msgs, 2) == 2) {
166 *ch = in_buf[0];
167 return true;
168 }
169
170 if (!ch7xxx->quiet) {
171 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to read register 0x%02x from %s:%02x.\n",
172 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
173 }
174 return false;
175}
176
177/** Writes an 8 bit register */
178static bool ch7xxx_writeb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t ch)
179{
180 struct ch7xxx_priv *ch7xxx = dvo->dev_priv;
181 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
182 uint8_t out_buf[2];
183 struct i2c_msg msg = {
184 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
185 .flags = 0,
186 .len = 2,
187 .buf = out_buf,
188 };
189
190 out_buf[0] = addr;
191 out_buf[1] = ch;
192
193 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, &msg, 1) == 1)
194 return true;
195
196 if (!ch7xxx->quiet) {
197 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to write register 0x%02x to %s:%d.\n",
198 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
199 }
200
201 return false;
202}
203
204static bool ch7xxx_init(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
205 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
206{
207 /* this will detect the CH7xxx chip on the specified i2c bus */
208 struct ch7xxx_priv *ch7xxx;
209 uint8_t vendor, device;
210 const char *name, *devid;
211
212 ch7xxx = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ch7xxx_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
213 if (ch7xxx == NULL)
214 return false;
215
216 dvo->i2c_bus = adapter;
217 dvo->dev_priv = ch7xxx;
218 ch7xxx->quiet = true;
219
220 if (!ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_REG_VID, &vendor))
221 goto out;
222
223 name = ch7xxx_get_id(vendor);
224 if (!name) {
225 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ch7xxx not detected; got 0x%02x from %s "
226 "slave %d.\n",
227 vendor, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
228 goto out;
229 }
230
231
232 if (!ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_REG_DID, &device))
233 goto out;
234
235 devid = ch7xxx_get_did(device);
236 if (!devid) {
237 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ch7xxx not detected; got 0x%02x from %s "
238 "slave %d.\n",
239 vendor, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
240 goto out;
241 }
242
243 ch7xxx->quiet = false;
244 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Detected %s chipset, vendor/device ID 0x%02x/0x%02x\n",
245 name, vendor, device);
246 return true;
247out:
248 kfree(ch7xxx);
249 return false;
250}
251
252static enum drm_connector_status ch7xxx_detect(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
253{
254 uint8_t cdet, orig_pm, pm;
255
256 ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, &orig_pm);
257
258 pm = orig_pm;
259 pm &= ~CH7xxx_PM_FPD;
260 pm |= CH7xxx_PM_DVIL | CH7xxx_PM_DVIP;
261
262 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, pm);
263
264 ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_CONNECTION_DETECT, &cdet);
265
266 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, orig_pm);
267
268 if (cdet & CH7xxx_CDET_DVI)
269 return connector_status_connected;
270 return connector_status_disconnected;
271}
272
273static enum drm_mode_status ch7xxx_mode_valid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
274 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
275{
276 if (mode->clock > 165000)
277 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
278
279 return MODE_OK;
280}
281
282static void ch7xxx_mode_set(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
283 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
284 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
285{
286 uint8_t tvco, tpcp, tpd, tlpf, idf;
287
288 if (mode->clock <= 65000) {
289 tvco = 0x23;
290 tpcp = 0x08;
291 tpd = 0x16;
292 tlpf = 0x60;
293 } else {
294 tvco = 0x2d;
295 tpcp = 0x06;
296 tpd = 0x26;
297 tlpf = 0xa0;
298 }
299
300 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TCTL, 0x00);
301 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TVCO, tvco);
302 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TPCP, tpcp);
303 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TPD, tpd);
304 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TPVT, 0x30);
305 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TLPF, tlpf);
306 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_TCT, 0x00);
307
308 ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_IDF, &idf);
309
310 idf &= ~(CH7xxx_IDF_HSP | CH7xxx_IDF_VSP);
311 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC)
312 idf |= CH7xxx_IDF_HSP;
313
314 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC)
315 idf |= CH7xxx_IDF_VSP;
316
317 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_IDF, idf);
318}
319
320/* set the CH7xxx power state */
321static void ch7xxx_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable)
322{
323 if (enable)
324 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, CH7xxx_PM_DVIL | CH7xxx_PM_DVIP);
325 else
326 ch7xxx_writeb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, CH7xxx_PM_FPD);
327}
328
329static bool ch7xxx_get_hw_state(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
330{
331 u8 val;
332
333 ch7xxx_readb(dvo, CH7xxx_PM, &val);
334
335 if (val & (CH7xxx_PM_DVIL | CH7xxx_PM_DVIP))
336 return true;
337 else
338 return false;
339}
340
341static void ch7xxx_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
342{
343 int i;
344
345 for (i = 0; i < CH7xxx_NUM_REGS; i++) {
346 uint8_t val;
347 if ((i % 8) == 0)
348 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("\n %02X: ", i);
349 ch7xxx_readb(dvo, i, &val);
350 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%02X ", val);
351 }
352}
353
354static void ch7xxx_destroy(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
355{
356 struct ch7xxx_priv *ch7xxx = dvo->dev_priv;
357
358 if (ch7xxx) {
359 kfree(ch7xxx);
360 dvo->dev_priv = NULL;
361 }
362}
363
364struct intel_dvo_dev_ops ch7xxx_ops = {
365 .init = ch7xxx_init,
366 .detect = ch7xxx_detect,
367 .mode_valid = ch7xxx_mode_valid,
368 .mode_set = ch7xxx_mode_set,
369 .dpms = ch7xxx_dpms,
370 .get_hw_state = ch7xxx_get_hw_state,
371 .dump_regs = ch7xxx_dump_regs,
372 .destroy = ch7xxx_destroy,
373};
